			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				I do like the idea about the 2hr non tradable.  You could also have it so that if the PKs friend does kill him to loot the item you just lost, a message pops up saying so and so now has your item, therefore you can track where your item is headed, then can ask for it or kill the next guy for it.  But then the problem of the person who killed you is 5lvls above you and then the guy who killed him is 5lvls above the original PK, then being outta range of you lvl spread.  So to solve that maybe you could have it where the item just obtained cannot be looted by anyone whe kills the original PK, or that item cannot be looted by someone out of your lvl range.  All good Ideas.  Here is one I had, what if when you start the lvl spread is not as much, but the higher you get the bigger the spread gets, until you hit lvl 20 where it becomes the full set gap such as 5lvl (example)  this would cut down on lvl 1 getting stomped by lvl 8.  Here is the other part of the Loot structure you must quest to become more than just coin only.  Say for instance you are coin only from lvl 1-10 but at lvl 10 you can quest to become coin and 1 item, and at lvl 20 you can quest to become coin, 1 item in bag or not.  Hence you have to progress to become a great PK.  1)  Also if you are a PK with coin and 1 item loot and your prey is coin only you would only be able to loot the coin.  2) if you are a PK with coin only and your prey is coin and item you only get the coin.  3) if you are a PK with coin and item and your prey is the same you of course get the coin and item.  I think this way you have a choice whether or not how much risk you would like to take.  Also PK will be happy the got someone with an item or kick themselves in the butt for targeting a coin only person.  Another thing is for the 2hr non-tradable items, the PKer involved should not be able to go anon atleast to you, you should be able to know what zone they are in so you can chase them down if you choose. <br> As far as the lvl gap goes I think 8 lvls is too much.  Should be 4 or 5 lvls, but in a group if the highest person is in your range say for instance you are lvl 20 and the highest lvl in group is lvl 25, your lvl 25 groupmate gets attack by a lvl 30, you then take on your groupmates range which is a 10 lvl difference to you. that way the person trying to PK your highest member does not get off the easy by not having to worry about you helping.  The lvl difference as I had mentioned before should be lower at lower lvls until lvl 20, it should go as follows or something like it lvl 1-4 (1 lvl spread), 5-9 (2lvl spread), 10-14 (3lvl spread), 15-19 (4lvl spread), then finally 20+ (5lvl spread).  Having it this way does 2 great things A) keeps chances of actually repelling a PK from slaughtering you, hence making it harder and more of a much needed challenge to be a successfull PK  B)  Keeps the group focus Verant wants, not to mention if you want to have all group members effective you will group with ppl closer to your lvl.  but doesn't elimate having groups with lvl ranges more than 5lvl between them.  Well enough talk from me I think these are fair and great ideas for everyone.  PKing should be apart of the PvP roleplaying but PKing shouldn't be easy, PKing should be somewhat of a challenge for those who try to pursue it.		

